Post leg( quad/ anterior focus ) hypertrophy workout
15 min of “flow work”
Got the heart rate going and kept it steady—- medium intensity day !

I personally love adding kettlebells with strength and conditioning work… we gotta be careful with falling in love with “fixed” objects in singular planes… sure the bulk of our BIG movements are done with barbell, but I love using other modalities to achieve a desired stimulus. 

In my Small Groups, we are now entering week 3 of this hypertrophy block( muscle building focus). Pair this with a DIRECTED eating plan and the SKY is the limit…

Everything has its season… max strength, hypertrophy, endurance, eating in a surplus, maintenance, and dieting down… spend time in each and keep your training structured and with metrics! 

Want more info on how I change bodies? Hit me. I will be opening up some PM small group training slots soon, so ya better get in NOW!

Good day comrades and never stop learning!!!!

Drop sets can be great for hypertrophy and increasing muscle size. In order for growth there needs to be sufficient stress to elicit muscle fiber recruitment. For those who claim they want an increase in lean tissue aka muscle, I most commonly see way too many ramp up ssts and enough “WORKING” sets. If you have more than 2-3 reps in the tank, you ain’t working hard enough… it’s just that simple. Carry that mentality and focus on the quality of your lifting sessions and  it just “checking off numbers”

“In progressive overload we trust, amen!”
